                    <span>If you want a real reference book for .Net programming, this is it.  He goes into depth in explaining how things work.  Especially liked his chapter on Multithreading.  It is a gold-mine for a professional C# programmer.
<br />
<br />PS.  The guy who gave this book a low rating, probably hasn't done anything sophisticated with .Net yet.  Hey, its a reference book and his writing style is clear and to the point.</span>
                  
